subSubSection.paragraph:
Primordial copulatory organ. Pre-epigyne: Pre-septum (pre-MS) with one posterior transversal edge. Anterior margins of pre-MS visible as two small longitudinal edges (
Fig. 75f
) below anterior margins of pre-lateral lobes. Distance between the two endings of the former longer than half the length of pre-MS.

Variation of copulatory organs.
Females: Distal tips of the branches of tegimentum (TM) may be directed further medially (
Fig. 75e
). Posterior section of MS may be shorter (
Fig. 75e
). Direction of SH may differ slightly (
Fig. 75d
).
